249static int
250do_preproc_only(void)
251{
252 yasm_linemap *linemap;
253 char *preproc_buf;
254 size_t got;
255 const char *base_filename;
256 FILE *out = NULL;
257 yasm_errwarns *errwarns = yasm_errwarns_create();
258
259 /* Initialize line map */
260 linemap = yasm_linemap_create();
261 yasm_linemap_set(linemap, in_filename, 0, 1, 1);
262
263 /* Default output to stdout if not specified or generating dependency
264 makefiles */
265 if (!obj_filename || generate_make_dependencies) {
266 out = stdout;
267
268 /* determine the object filename if not specified, but we need a
269 file name for the makefile rule */
270 if (generate_make_dependencies && !obj_filename) {
271 if (in_filename == NULL)
272 /* Default to yasm.out if no obj filename specified */
273 obj_filename = yasm__xstrdup("yasm.out");
274 else {
275 /* replace (or add) extension to base filename */
276 yasm__splitpath(in_filename, &base_filename);
277 if (base_filename[0] == '\0')
278 obj_filename = yasm__xstrdup("yasm.out");
279 else
280 obj_filename = replace_extension(base_filename,
281 cur_objfmt_module->extension, "yasm.out");
282 }
283 }
284 } else {
285 /* Open output (object) file */
286 out = open_file(obj_filename, "wt");
287 if (!out)
288 return EXIT_FAILURE;
289 }
290
291 /* Create preprocessor */
292 cur_preproc = yasm_preproc_create(cur_preproc_module, in_filename, NULL,
293 linemap, errwarns);
294
295 /* Apply macros */
296 apply_preproc_builtins();
297 apply_preproc_standard_macros(cur_parser_module->stdmacs);
298 apply_preproc_standard_macros(cur_objfmt_module->stdmacs);
299 apply_preproc_saved_options();
300
301 /* Pre-process until done */
302 if (generate_make_dependencies) {
303 size_t totlen;
304
305 preproc_buf = yasm_xmalloc(PREPROC_BUF_SIZE);
306
307 fprintf(stdout, "%s: %s", obj_filename, in_filename);
308 totlen = strlen(obj_filename)+2+strlen(in_filename);
309
310 while ((got = yasm_preproc_get_included_file(cur_preproc, preproc_buf,
311 PREPROC_BUF_SIZE)) != 0) {
312 totlen += got;
313 if (totlen > 72) {
314 fputs(" \\\n ", stdout);
315 totlen = 2;
316 }
317 fputc(' ', stdout);
318 fwrite(preproc_buf, got, 1, stdout);
319 }
320 fputc('\n', stdout);
321 yasm_xfree(preproc_buf);
322 } else {
323 while ((preproc_buf = yasm_preproc_get_line(cur_preproc)) != NULL) {
324 fputs(preproc_buf, out);
325 fputc('\n', out);
326 yasm_xfree(preproc_buf);
327 }
328 }
329
330 if (out != stdout)
331 fclose(out);
332
333 if (yasm_errwarns_num_errors(errwarns, warning_error) > 0) {
334 yasm_errwarns_output_all(errwarns, linemap, warning_error,
335 print_yasm_error, print_yasm_warning);
336 if (out != stdout)
337 remove(obj_filename);
338 yasm_linemap_destroy(linemap);
339 yasm_errwarns_destroy(errwarns);
340 cleanup(NULL);
341 return EXIT_FAILURE;
342 }
343
344 yasm_errwarns_output_all(errwarns, linemap, warning_error,
345 print_yasm_error, print_yasm_warning);
346 yasm_linemap_destroy(linemap);
347 yasm_errwarns_destroy(errwarns);
348 cleanup(NULL);
349 return EXIT_SUCCESS;
350}
351
352static int
353do_assemble(void)
354{
355 yasm_object *object;
356 const char *base_filename;
357 /*@null@*/ FILE *obj = NULL;
358 yasm_arch_create_error arch_error;
359 yasm_linemap *linemap;
360 yasm_errwarns *errwarns = yasm_errwarns_create();
361 int i, matched;
362 const char *machine;
363
364 /* Initialize line map */
365 linemap = yasm_linemap_create();
366 yasm_linemap_set(linemap, in_filename, 0, 1, 1);
367
368 /* determine the object filename if not specified */
369 if (!obj_filename) {
370 if (in_filename == NULL)
371 /* Default to yasm.out if no obj filename specified */
372 obj_filename = yasm__xstrdup("yasm.out");
373 else {
374 /* replace (or add) extension to base filename */
375 yasm__splitpath(in_filename, &base_filename);
376 if (base_filename[0] == '\0')
377 obj_filename = yasm__xstrdup("yasm.out");
378 else
379 obj_filename = replace_extension(base_filename,
380 cur_objfmt_module->extension,
381 "yasm.out");
382 }
383 }
384
385 /* Set up architecture using machine and parser. */
386 if (!machine_name) {
387 /* If we're using x86 and the default objfmt bits is 64, default the
388 * machine to amd64. When we get more arches with multiple machines,
389 * we should do this in a more modular fashion.
390 */
391 if (strcmp(cur_arch_module->keyword, "x86") == 0 &&
392 cur_objfmt_module->default_x86_mode_bits == 64)
393 machine_name = yasm__xstrdup("amd64");
394 else
395 machine_name =
396 yasm__xstrdup(cur_arch_module->default_machine_keyword);
397 }
398
399 /* If we're using amd64 and the default objfmt is elfx32, change the
400 * machine to "x32".
401 */
402 if (strcmp(machine_name, "amd64") == 0 &&
403 strcmp(cur_objfmt_module->keyword, "elfx32") == 0)
404 machine = "x32";
405 else
406 machine = machine_name;
407
408 cur_arch = yasm_arch_create(cur_arch_module, machine,
409 cur_parser_module->keyword, &arch_error);
410 if (!cur_arch) {
411 switch (arch_error) {
412 case YASM_ARCH_CREATE_BAD_MACHINE:
413 print_error(_("%s: `%s' is not a valid %s for %s `%s'"),
414 _("FATAL"), machine_name, _("machine"),
415 _("architecture"), cur_arch_module->keyword);
416 break;
417 case YASM_ARCH_CREATE_BAD_PARSER:
418 print_error(_("%s: `%s' is not a valid %s for %s `%s'"),
419 _("FATAL"), cur_parser_module->keyword,
420 _("parser"), _("architecture"),
421 cur_arch_module->keyword);
422 break;
423 default:
424 print_error(_("%s: unknown architecture error"), _("FATAL"));
425 }
426
427 return EXIT_FAILURE;
428 }
429
430 /* Create object */
431 object = yasm_object_create(in_filename, obj_filename, cur_arch,
432 cur_objfmt_module, cur_dbgfmt_module);
433 if (!object) {
434 yasm_error_class eclass;
435 unsigned long xrefline;
436 /*@only@*/ /*@null@*/ char *estr, *xrefstr;
437
438 yasm_error_fetch(&eclass, &estr, &xrefline, &xrefstr);
439 print_error("%s: %s", _("FATAL"), estr);
440 yasm_xfree(estr);
441 yasm_xfree(xrefstr);
442
443 cleanup(object);
444 return EXIT_FAILURE;
445 }
446
447 /* Get a fresh copy of objfmt_module as it may have changed. */
448 cur_objfmt_module = ((yasm_objfmt_base *)object->objfmt)->module;
449
450 /* Check to see if the requested preprocessor is in the allowed list
451 * for the active parser.
452 */
453 matched = 0;
454 for (i=0; cur_parser_module->preproc_keywords[i]; i++)
455 {
456 if (yasm__strcasecmp(cur_parser_module->preproc_keywords[i],
457 cur_preproc_module->keyword) == 0) {
458 matched = 1;
459 break;
460 }
461 }
462
463 if (!matched) {
464 print_error(_("%s: `%s' is not a valid %s for %s `%s'"), _("FATAL"),
465 cur_preproc_module->keyword, _("preprocessor"),
466 _("parser"), cur_parser_module->keyword);
467 cleanup(object);
468 return EXIT_FAILURE;
469 }
470
471 if (global_prefix)
472 yasm_object_set_global_prefix(object, global_prefix);
473 if (global_suffix)
474 yasm_object_set_global_suffix(object, global_suffix);
475
476 cur_preproc = yasm_preproc_create(cur_preproc_module, in_filename,
477 object->symtab, linemap, errwarns);
478
479 apply_preproc_builtins();
480 apply_preproc_standard_macros(cur_parser_module->stdmacs);
481 apply_preproc_standard_macros(cur_objfmt_module->stdmacs);
482 apply_preproc_saved_options();
483
484 /* Get initial x86 BITS setting from object format */
485 if (strcmp(cur_arch_module->keyword, "x86") == 0) {
486 yasm_arch_set_var(cur_arch, "mode_bits",
487 cur_objfmt_module->default_x86_mode_bits);
488 }
489
490 yasm_arch_set_var(cur_arch, "force_strict", force_strict);
491
492 /* Try to enable the map file via a map NASM directive. This is
493 * somewhat of a hack.
494 */
495 if (map_filename) {
496 const yasm_directive *dir = &cur_objfmt_module->directives[0];
497 matched = 0;
498 for (; dir && dir->name; dir++) {
499 if (yasm__strcasecmp(dir->name, "map") == 0 &&
500 yasm__strcasecmp(dir->parser, "nasm") == 0) {
501 yasm_valparamhead vps;
502 yasm_valparam *vp;
503 matched = 1;
504 yasm_vps_initialize(&vps);
505 vp = yasm_vp_create_string(NULL, yasm__xstrdup(map_filename));
506 yasm_vps_append(&vps, vp);
507 dir->handler(object, &vps, NULL, 0);
508 yasm_vps_delete(&vps);
509 }
510 }
511 if (!matched) {
512 print_error(
513 _("warning: object format `%s' does not support map files"),
514 cur_objfmt_module->keyword);
515 }
516 }
517
518 /* Parse! */
519 cur_parser_module->do_parse(object, cur_preproc, list_filename != NULL,
520 linemap, errwarns);
521
522 check_errors(errwarns, object, linemap);
523
524 /* Finalize parse */
525 yasm_object_finalize(object, errwarns);
526 check_errors(errwarns, object, linemap);
527
528 /* Optimize */
529 yasm_object_optimize(object, errwarns);
530 check_errors(errwarns, object, linemap);
531
532 /* generate any debugging information */
533 yasm_dbgfmt_generate(object, linemap, errwarns);
534 check_errors(errwarns, object, linemap);
535
536 /* open the object file for output (if not already opened by dbg objfmt) */
537 if (!obj && strcmp(cur_objfmt_module->keyword, "dbg") != 0) {
538 obj = open_file(obj_filename, "wb");
539 if (!obj) {
540 cleanup(object);
541 return EXIT_FAILURE;
542 }
543 }
544
545 /* Write the object file */
546 yasm_objfmt_output(object, obj?obj:stderr,
547 strcmp(cur_dbgfmt_module->keyword, "null"), errwarns);
548
549 /* Close object file */
550 if (obj)
551 fclose(obj);
552
553 /* If we had an error at this point, we also need to delete the output
554 * object file (to make sure it's not left newer than the source).
555 */
556 if (yasm_errwarns_num_errors(errwarns, warning_error) > 0)
557 remove(obj_filename);
558 check_errors(errwarns, object, linemap);
559
560 /* Open and write the list file */
561 if (list_filename) {
562 FILE *list = open_file(list_filename, "wt");
563 if (!list) {
564 cleanup(object);
565 return EXIT_FAILURE;
566 }
567 /* Initialize the list format */
568 cur_listfmt = yasm_listfmt_create(cur_listfmt_module, in_filename,
569 obj_filename);
570 yasm_listfmt_output(cur_listfmt, list, linemap, cur_arch);
571 fclose(list);
572 }
573
574 yasm_errwarns_output_all(errwarns, linemap, warning_error,
575 print_yasm_error, print_yasm_warning);
576
577 yasm_linemap_destroy(linemap);
578 yasm_errwarns_destroy(errwarns);
579 cleanup(object);
580 return EXIT_SUCCESS;
581}

583/* main function */
584/*@-globstate -unrecog@*/
585int
586main(int argc, char *argv[])
587{
588 size_t i;
589
590 errfile = stderr;
591
592#if defined(HAVE_SETLOCALE) && defined(HAVE_LC_MESSAGES)
593 setlocale(LC_MESSAGES, "");
594#endif
595#if defined(LOCALEDIR)
596 bindtextdomain(PACKAGE, LOCALEDIR);
597#endif
598 textdomain(PACKAGE);
599
600 /* Initialize errwarn handling */
601 yasm_internal_error_ = handle_yasm_int_error;
602 yasm_fatal = handle_yasm_fatal;
603 yasm_gettext_hook = handle_yasm_gettext;
604 yasm_errwarn_initialize();
605
606 /* Initialize BitVector (needed for intnum/floatnum). */
607 if (BitVector_Boot() != ErrCode_Ok) {
608 print_error(_("%s: could not initialize BitVector"), _("FATAL"));
609 return EXIT_FAILURE;
610 }
611
612 /* Initialize intnum and floatnum */
613 yasm_intnum_initialize();
614 yasm_floatnum_initialize();
615
616#ifdef CMAKE_BUILD
617 /* Load standard modules */
618#ifdef BUILD_SHARED_LIBS
619 if (!load_plugin("yasmstd")) {
620 print_error(_("%s: could not load standard modules"), _("FATAL"));
621 return EXIT_FAILURE;
622 }
623#else
624 yasm_init_plugin();
625#endif
626#endif
627
628 /* Initialize parameter storage */
629 STAILQ_INIT(&preproc_options);
630
631 if (parse_cmdline(argc, argv, options, NELEMS(options), print_error))
632 return EXIT_FAILURE;
633
634 switch (special_options) {
635 case SPECIAL_SHOW_HELP:
636 /* Does gettext calls internally */
637 help_msg(help_head, help_tail, options, NELEMS(options));
638 return EXIT_SUCCESS;
639 case SPECIAL_SHOW_VERSION:
640 for (i=0; i<NELEMS(version_msg); i++)
641 printf("%s\n", version_msg[i]);
642 return EXIT_SUCCESS;
643 case SPECIAL_SHOW_LICENSE:
644 for (i=0; i<NELEMS(license_msg); i++)
645 printf("%s\n", license_msg[i]);
646 return EXIT_SUCCESS;
647 case SPECIAL_LISTED:
648 /* Printed out earlier */
649 return EXIT_SUCCESS;
650 }
651
652 /* Open error file if specified. */
653 if (error_filename) {
654 errfile = open_file(error_filename, "wt");
655 if (!errfile)
656 return EXIT_FAILURE;
657 }
658
659 /* If not already specified, default to bin as the object format. */
660 if (!cur_objfmt_module) {
661 if (!objfmt_keyword)
662 objfmt_keyword = yasm__xstrdup("bin");
663 cur_objfmt_module = yasm_load_objfmt(objfmt_keyword);
664 if (!cur_objfmt_module) {
665 print_error(_("%s: could not load default %s"), _("FATAL"),
666 _("object format"));
667 return EXIT_FAILURE;
668 }
669 }
670
671 /* Default to x86 as the architecture */
672 if (!cur_arch_module) {
673 cur_arch_module = yasm_load_arch("x86");
674 if (!cur_arch_module) {
675 print_error(_("%s: could not load default %s"), _("FATAL"),
676 _("architecture"));
677 return EXIT_FAILURE;
678 }
679 }
680
681 /* Check for arch help */
682 if (machine_name && strcmp(machine_name, "help") == 0) {
683 const yasm_arch_machine *m = cur_arch_module->machines;
684 printf(_("Available %s for %s `%s':\n"), _("machines"),
685 _("architecture"), cur_arch_module->keyword);
686 while (m->keyword && m->name) {
687 print_list_keyword_desc(m->name, m->keyword);
688 m++;
689 }
690 return EXIT_SUCCESS;
691 }
692
693 /* Default to NASM as the parser */
694 if (!cur_parser_module) {
695 cur_parser_module = yasm_load_parser("nasm");
696 if (!cur_parser_module) {
697 print_error(_("%s: could not load default %s"), _("FATAL"),
698 _("parser"));
699 cleanup(NULL);
700 return EXIT_FAILURE;
701 }
702 }
703
704 /* If not already specified, default to the parser's default preproc. */
705 if (!cur_preproc_module) {
706 cur_preproc_module =
707 yasm_load_preproc(cur_parser_module->default_preproc_keyword);
708 if (!cur_preproc_module) {
709 print_error(_("%s: could not load default %s"), _("FATAL"),
710 _("preprocessor"));
711 cleanup(NULL);
712 return EXIT_FAILURE;
713 }
714 }
715
716 /* Determine input filename and open input file. */
717 if (!in_filename) {
718 print_error(_("No input files specified"));
719 return EXIT_FAILURE;
720 }
721
722 /* handle preproc-only case here */
723 if (preproc_only)
724 return do_preproc_only();
725
726 /* If list file enabled, make sure we have a list format loaded. */
727 if (list_filename) {
728 /* If not already specified, default to nasm as the list format. */
729 if (!cur_listfmt_module) {
730 cur_listfmt_module = yasm_load_listfmt("nasm");
731 if (!cur_listfmt_module) {
732 print_error(_("%s: could not load default %s"), _("FATAL"),
733 _("list format"));
734 return EXIT_FAILURE;
735 }
736 }
737 }
738
739 /* If not already specified, default to null as the debug format. */
740 if (!cur_dbgfmt_module) {
741 cur_dbgfmt_module = yasm_load_dbgfmt("null");
742 if (!cur_dbgfmt_module) {
743 print_error(_("%s: could not load default %s"), _("FATAL"),
744 _("debug format"));
745 return EXIT_FAILURE;
746 }
747 }
748
749 return do_assemble();
750}
751/*@=globstate =unrecog@*/

753/* Open the object file. Returns 0 on failure. */
754static FILE *
755open_file(const char *filename, const char *mode)
756{
757 FILE *f;
758
759 f = fopen(filename, mode);
760 if (!f)
761 print_error(_("could not open file `%s'"), filename);
762 return f;
763}

765static void
766check_errors(yasm_errwarns *errwarns, yasm_object *object,
767 yasm_linemap *linemap)
768{
769 if (yasm_errwarns_num_errors(errwarns, warning_error) > 0) {
770 yasm_errwarns_output_all(errwarns, linemap, warning_error,
771 print_yasm_error, print_yasm_warning);
772 yasm_linemap_destroy(linemap);
773 yasm_errwarns_destroy(errwarns);
774 cleanup(object);
775 exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
776 }
777}
778
779/* Define DO_FREE to 1 to enable deallocation of all data structures.
780 * Useful for detecting memory leaks, but slows down execution unnecessarily
781 * (as the OS will free everything we miss here).
782 */
783#define DO_FREE 1
784
785/* Cleans up all allocated structures. */
786static void
787cleanup(yasm_object *object)
788{
789 if (DO_FREE) {
790 if (cur_listfmt)
791 yasm_listfmt_destroy(cur_listfmt);
792 if (cur_preproc)
793 yasm_preproc_destroy(cur_preproc);
794 if (object)
795 yasm_object_destroy(object);
796
797 yasm_floatnum_cleanup();
798 yasm_intnum_cleanup();
799
800 yasm_errwarn_cleanup();
801
802 BitVector_Shutdown();
803 }
804
805 if (DO_FREE) {
806 if (in_filename)
807 yasm_xfree(in_filename);
808 if (obj_filename)
809 yasm_xfree(obj_filename);
810 if (list_filename)
811 yasm_xfree(list_filename);
812 if (map_filename)
813 yasm_xfree(map_filename);
814 if (machine_name)
815 yasm_xfree(machine_name);
816 if (objfmt_keyword)
817 yasm_xfree(objfmt_keyword);
818 }
819
820 if (errfile != stderr && errfile != stdout)
821 fclose(errfile);
822#if defined(CMAKE_BUILD) && defined(BUILD_SHARED_LIBS)
823 unload_plugins();
824#endif
825}

844int
845other_option_handler(char *option)
846{
847 /* Accept, but ignore, -O and -Onnn, for compatibility with NASM. */
848 if (option[0] == '-' && option[1] == 'O') {
849 int n = 2;
850 for (;;) {
851 if (option[n] == '\0')
852 return 0;
853 if (!isdigit(option[n]))
854 return 1;
855 n++;
856 }
857 }
858 return 1;
859}

1060static int
1061opt_warning_handler(char *cmd, /*@unused@*/ char *param, int extra)
1062{
1063 /* is it disabling the warning instead of enabling? */
1064 void (*action)(yasm_warn_class wclass) = yasm_warn_enable;
1065
1066 if (extra == 1) {
1067 /* -w, disable warnings */
1068 yasm_warn_disable_all();
1069 return 0;
1070 }
1071
1072 /* skip past 'W' */
1073 cmd++;
1074
1075 /* detect no- prefix to disable the warning */
1076 if (cmd[0] == 'n' && cmd[1] == 'o' && cmd[2] == '-') {
1077 action = yasm_warn_disable;
1078 cmd += 3; /* skip past it to get to the warning name */
1079 }
1080
1081 if (cmd[0] == '\0')
1082 /* just -W or -Wno-, so definitely not valid */
1083 return 1;
1084 else if (strcmp(cmd, "error") == 0)
1085 warning_error = (action == yasm_warn_enable);
1086 else if (strcmp(cmd, "unrecognized-char") == 0)
1087 action(YASM_WARN_UNREC_CHAR);
1088 else if (strcmp(cmd, "orphan-labels") == 0)
1089 action(YASM_WARN_ORPHAN_LABEL);
1090 else if (strcmp(cmd, "uninit-contents") == 0)
1091 action(YASM_WARN_UNINIT_CONTENTS);
1092 else if (strcmp(cmd, "size-override") == 0)
1093 action(YASM_WARN_SIZE_OVERRIDE);
1094 else
1095 return 1;
1096
1097 return 0;
1098}

1214static void
1215apply_preproc_builtins()
1216{
1217 char *predef;
1218
1219 /* Define standard YASM assembly-time macro constants */
1220 predef = yasm_xmalloc(strlen("__YASM_OBJFMT__=")
1221 + strlen(objfmt_keyword) + 1);
1222 strcpy(predef, "__YASM_OBJFMT__=");
1223 strcat(predef, objfmt_keyword);
1224 yasm_preproc_define_builtin(cur_preproc, predef);
1225 yasm_xfree(predef);
1226}
1227
1228static void
1229apply_preproc_standard_macros(const yasm_stdmac *stdmacs)
1230{
1231 int i, matched;
1232
1233 if (!stdmacs)
1234 return;
1235
1236 matched = -1;
1237 for (i=0; stdmacs[i].parser; i++)
1238 if (yasm__strcasecmp(stdmacs[i].parser,
1239 cur_parser_module->keyword) == 0 &&
1240 yasm__strcasecmp(stdmacs[i].preproc,
1241 cur_preproc_module->keyword) == 0)
1242 matched = i;
1243 if (matched >= 0 && stdmacs[matched].macros)
1244 yasm_preproc_add_standard(cur_preproc, stdmacs[matched].macros);
1245}
1246
1247static void
1248apply_preproc_saved_options()
1249{
1250 constcharparam *cp, *cpnext;
1251
1252 void (*funcs[3])(yasm_preproc *, const char *);
1253 funcs[0] = cur_preproc_module->add_include_file;
1254 funcs[1] = cur_preproc_module->predefine_macro;
1255 funcs[2] = cur_preproc_module->undefine_macro;
1256
1257 STAILQ_FOREACH(cp, &preproc_options, link) {
1258 if (0 <= cp->id && cp->id < 3 && funcs[cp->id])
1259 funcs[cp->id](cur_preproc, cp->param);
1260 }
1261
1262 cp = STAILQ_FIRST(&preproc_options);
1263 while (cp != NULL) {
1264 cpnext = STAILQ_NEXT(cp, link);
1265 yasm_xfree(cp);
1266 cp = cpnext;
1267 }
1268 STAILQ_INIT(&preproc_options);
1269}

1271/* Replace extension on a filename (or append one if none is present).
1272 * If output filename would be identical to input (same extension out as in),
1273 * returns (copy of) def.
1274 * A NULL ext means the trailing '.' should NOT be included, whereas a "" ext
1275 * means the trailing '.' should be included.
1276 */
1277static char *
1278replace_extension(const char *orig, /*@null@*/ const char *ext,
1279 const char *def)
1280{
1281 char *out, *outext;
1282 size_t deflen, outlen;
1283
1284 /* allocate enough space for full existing name + extension */
1285 outlen = strlen(orig) + 2;
1286 if (ext)
1287 outlen += strlen(ext) + 1;
1288 deflen = strlen(def) + 1;
1289 if (outlen < deflen)
1290 outlen = deflen;
1291 out = yasm_xmalloc(outlen);
1292
1293 strcpy(out, orig);
1294 outext = strrchr(out, '.');
1295 if (outext) {
1296 /* Existing extension: make sure it's not the same as the replacement
1297 * (as we don't want to overwrite the source file).
1298 */
1299 outext++; /* advance past '.' */
1300 if (ext && strcmp(outext, ext) == 0) {
1301 outext = NULL; /* indicate default should be used */
1302 print_error(
1303 _("file name already ends in `.%s': output will be in `%s'"),
1304 ext, def);
1305 }
1306 } else {
1307 /* No extension: make sure the output extension is not empty
1308 * (again, we don't want to overwrite the source file).
1309 */
1310 if (!ext)
1311 print_error(
1312 _("file name already has no extension: output will be in `%s'"),
1313 def);
1314 else {
1315 outext = strrchr(out, '\0'); /* point to end of the string */
1316 *outext++ = '.'; /* append '.' */
1317 }
1318 }
1319
1320 /* replace extension or use default name */
1321 if (outext) {
1322 if (!ext) {
1323 /* Back up and replace '.' with string terminator */
1324 outext--;
1325 *outext = '\0';
1326 } else
1327 strcpy(outext, ext);
1328 } else
1329 strcpy(out, def);
1330
1331 return out;
1332}
1333
1334void
1335print_list_keyword_desc(const char *name, const char *keyword)
1336{
1337 printf("%4s%-12s%s\n", "", keyword, name);
1338}

1340static void
1341print_error(const char *fmt, ...)
1342{
1343 va_list va;
1344 fprintf(errfile, "yasm: ");
1345 va_start(va, fmt);
1346 vfprintf(errfile, fmt, va);
1347 va_end(va);
1348 fputc('\n', errfile);
1349}

1351static /*@exits@*/ void
1352handle_yasm_int_error(const char *file, unsigned int line, const char *message)
1353{
1354 fprintf(stderr, _("INTERNAL ERROR at %s, line %u: %s\n"), file, line,
1355 gettext(message));
1356#ifdef HAVE_ABORT
1357 abort();
1358#else
1359 exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1360#endif
1361}

1363static /*@exits@*/ void
1364handle_yasm_fatal(const char *fmt, va_list va)
1365{
1366 fprintf(errfile, "yasm: %s: ", _("FATAL"));
1367 vfprintf(errfile, gettext(fmt), va);
1368 fputc('\n', errfile);
1369 exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1370}

1373handle_yasm_gettext(const char *msgid)
1374{

1378static const char *fmt[2] = {
1379 "%s:%lu: %s%s\n", /* GNU */
1380 "%s(%lu) : %s%s\n" /* VC */
1381};
1382
1383static const char *fmt_noline[2] = {
1384 "%s: %s%s\n", /* GNU */
1385 "%s : %s%s\n" /* VC */
1386};
1387
1388static void
1389print_yasm_error(const char *filename, unsigned long line, const char *msg,
1390 const char *xref_fn, unsigned long xref_line,
1391 const char *xref_msg)
1392{
1393 if (line)
1394 fprintf(errfile, fmt[ewmsg_style], filename, line, _("error: "), msg);
1395 else
1396 fprintf(errfile, fmt_noline[ewmsg_style], filename, _("error: "), msg);
1397
1398 if (xref_fn && xref_msg) {
1399 if (xref_line)
1400 fprintf(errfile, fmt[ewmsg_style], xref_fn, xref_line, _("error: "),
1401 xref_msg);
1402 else
1403 fprintf(errfile, fmt_noline[ewmsg_style], xref_fn, _("error: "),
1404 xref_msg);
1405 }
1406}

1408static void
1409print_yasm_warning(const char *filename, unsigned long line, const char *msg)
1410{
1411 if (line)
1412 fprintf(errfile, fmt[ewmsg_style], filename, line, _("warning: "),
1413 msg);
1414 else
1415 fprintf(errfile, fmt_noline[ewmsg_style], filename, _("warning: "),
1416 msg);
1417}
